  "text": "The basic pseudo code of the SS is illustrated in Algorithm 1. The SS consists of five component processes as described by [CITATION_1] [19]: 1) Diversification Generation Method. It is used to generate a collection of diverse initial solutions as an input. 2) Improvement Method. It is used to enhance the quality of a trial solution using any local search to explore the neighbors of a solution. 3) Reference Set Update Method. It is used to build and maintain a reference set consisting of elite solutions (both good quality and diverse), organized to provide structured solution combinations. The size of the set is usually not more than 20 solutions (10 good quality and 10 diverse solutions). The Reference Set presents a diversity of the search. 4) Subset Generation Method. It is used to select solutions from the reference set, to produce a subset of its solutions as a basis for creating combined solutions. The most common subset",
